label.value: vasculature of central nervous system plus retina

value.value: An anatomical structure that is located along the line dividing two regions of an anatomical structure.

Wall of organ which has as its parts the endocardium, myocardium , epicardium, and the cardiac septum, surrounded by the pericardial sac proper and is continuous with the walls of the systemic and pulmonary arterial and venous trees.
An artery that supplies oxygenated blood to the cystic duct.
A vein that drains the urethra.
Ovarian vein, each instance of which is a tributary  of some inferior vena cava that drains the right pampiniform plexus of some broad ligament.
Ovarian vein, each instance of which is a tributary  of some left renal vein that drains the left pampiniform plexus of some broad ligament.
A zone of skin that is part of the snout.
Subdivision of the head consisting of the pointed or rounded end or extremity of the snout.
A zone of skin that is part of the face.
A parenchyma that is part of a spleen.
An anatomical junction between two parts of the digestive tract.
Cartilage which is part of the axial skeleton.
Tooth that is attached to the premaxilla.
Process that is part of the supraoccipital. It is a posteriorly directed and unpaired median projection off the posterior margin of the supraoccipital bone.

definition.value: The supraoccipital crest may be small and restricted to the dorsal part of the supraoccipital, or may be large and long and extending ventrally to the dorsal margin of the foramen magnum. The supraoccipital crest may be a large process extending above the skull roof in some teleostean subgroups.

value.value: Joint that articulates the left and right premaxillary bones. Inter-premaxillary joint is unpaired.
Centrum that is part of vertebra 2.
Joint that articulates the premaxilla and maxilla. Premaxillary-maxillary joint is paired.

Capillary that has pores in the endothelial cells (60-80 nm in diameter) that are spanned by a diaphragm of radially oriented fibrils and allow small molecules and limited amounts of protein to diffuse.
Non neural ectoderm that surrounds the presumptive neural plate and gives rise to neurogenic placodes.

label.value: preorbital process of the pars facialis of the maxilla

value.value: Anterior rod that articulates with the sacrum.
Semi-elliptical ball located at the lower end of the humerus, adjacent to the humeral ball.
Furrow between the humeral head and the ulnar condyle.
Lateral portion of the proximal (upper) articular surface of the radius that consists of an eminence with a rounded apex.
Structures of the dermis, epidermis, glands and pigment cells recognizable on the external surfaces of the integument.
